<br>
Saddam didn't pose an immediate threat to the outside world only to his own people, I agree with that.  It was becoming obvious that the world was not going to stand for it, but the US jumped the gun.  Support was long in coming, but we could not validly claim we needed to invade when we did, and the repercussions of that are becoming apparent now.<br>
