Okay, I've read it three times now. I think you were trying to make a link between Saddam using WMDs and Osama's hideouts in Afghanistan, but I'm not sure any such link has been implied, so I'm not sure what conclusions you draw from the lack of such evidence. If Al-qaeda is making WMDs, I'd think Afghanistan would be a poor short or long term choice for storage, considering the lack of relative security and infrastructure compared to, say, Iran or Saudi Arabia. <br>
<br>
More broadly, I don't think any proof of a WMD program makes Al-qaeda any more or less dangerous. They seem to do fine with commercial aircraft.<br>
