First of all, he is not saying 'do nothing about terrorism', which is a distinction you are not drawing when you make your statement.<br>
<br>
Second of all, thinking that 'doing something' against terrorism will always be better than doing nothing is fundamentally wrong. (I'm not going to conclude that we should, or should do not do nothing just to make it clear).<br>
<br>
Lets say, there are 10,000 Extreme individuals, who are determined to carry out Attacks on US Interests because America are evil.<br>
<br>
Lets say, also, you have 10,000,000 non-extreme indivuals who dislike America, but are not prepared to carry out attacks on the US.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
America launches an attack on the 10,000, and manage to break up their main base of operations, kill or capture 7,500 of those people.<br>
<br>
Now, the remaining 2,500 become even more furvored, and even more cunning about planning attacks.<br>
<br>
Also, 100,000 of the non-extreme people who dislike America are angered by what America did (rightly or wrongly), and when approached, or off their own bat, turn to extreme indivudlas, determined to strike at the interests of those they have now come to hate.<br>
<br>
Also 20,000,000 who are non-extreme and didn't mind america now dislike america.<br>
<br>
So, now, you have 102,500 terrorists prepare to carry out attacks on Americans up from 10,000 as a direct consequence of your actions.<br>
<br>
Finally. You are so astoundingly stupid to presume that suicide bombers, and terrorists actually care about what they can get away with.<br>
<br>
How the fuck do you deter someone who is willing to give their life for something?<br>
Seriously?<br>
<br>
&quot;If you kill yourself, we'll put you in prison!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;If you kill yourself, we'll execute you!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I won't become a suicide bomber, because If while I'm willing end my life by blowing my body into thousands of peices of bloody flesh in some car, I'm not willing to have American soldiers searching my house and finding my Yasser Arafat Porno&quot;<br>
<br>
It's not like you can commit a suicide bombing twice anyways.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
